   <text xml:space="preserve"><body><div type="edition" xml:lang="san-Latn" rendition="class:83233 maturity:83213">
            <lg met="āryā" n="0">
            <l n=""><lb n="1"/>śrīcampeśvaravijayī <unclear>m</unclear>ahāmatiś śrī<lb n="2" break="no"/>prakāśadharmmeti</l> 
            <l n="">sthāpitavān amareśa<unclear>ṁ</unclear> mahā<gap reason="illegible" quantity="4-5" unit="character"/></l>
            </lg>
         </div><div type="apparatus"><listApp><app loc="a"><lem>śrīcampeśvara°</lem><rdg source="bib:Huber1911_01">śrī campeśvaro</rdg></app><app loc="b"><lem><unclear>m</unclear>ahāmatiś śrī°</lem><rdg source="bib:Huber1911_01">mahīpati ... śrī</rdg></app><app loc="b"><lem>amareśa<unclear>ṁ</unclear> mahā<gap reason="illegible" quantity="4-5" unit="character"/></lem><rdg source="bib:Huber1911_01">amareśam iha ...</rdg></app></listApp></div><div type="translation"><p>The illustrious conqueror, king of Campā, of great wisdom, called Śrī Prakāśadharman, has established Amareśa, the great...</p></div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fra"><p>L’illustre conquérant, roi du Campā, de grande sagesse, appelé Śrī Prakāśadharman, a établi Amareśa, le grand...</p></div><div type="commentary"><p>It was not recognized by Huber that the inscription is metrical. Insufficient materials are at our disposal at this time to establish the whole text, but what is clear is that it concerns the erection of Amareśa, no doubt a <foreign>liṅga</foreign> of Śiva. Cf. <bibl><ptr target="bib:Bisschop2006_01"/><citedRange unit="page">33 with n. 79</citedRange></bibl></p></div><div type="bibliography"><p>First published, with French translation, in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Huber1911_01"/><citedRange unit="page">261</citedRange></bibl>; whence, with English translation, in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Majumdar1985_01"/><citedRange unit="page">15</citedRange></bibl>, whence <bibl><ptr target="bib:Golzio2004_01"/><citedRange unit="page">10</citedRange></bibl> Re-edited from the inked EFEO estampages and available photos, with new translation, in <bibl><ptr target="bib:Goodall+Griffiths2013_01"/><citedRange unit="page">427-428</citedRange></bibl>, whence the present edition.</p><listBibl type="primary"><bibl/></listBibl><listBibl type="secondary"><bibl><ptr target="bib:Parmentier1918_01"/><citedRange unit="page">439 and 587</citedRange></bibl></listBibl></div></body></text>
